review_blob: Black pour from 22oz bottle at home. Malty, cocoa, hints of coffee. Smooth and easy drinking. Roasty and bitter finish
Has an odd smokey and flower aroma to it. The taste is massive - almost feels like drinking suntan lotion. Flower, hibiscus, coconut, and tropical. Pretty good. Orange pour from 22oz bottle at home.
Orange pour from 22oz bottle at home. White head. Malty and a little dull. Some grapefruit and hops. Dank basement characteristics.
Black pour from draft at Bru in cincy. Creamy white head. Black licorice. Malty. Good hops and vanilla kick. I like
Orange pour from draft at Bru in cincy. Tons of foamy white head. Grapefruit and bitter. Malty. Pine. Not bad
Orange bright pour from draft at their brewery. Hoppy and a little off. Big fruity profile. Grapefruit and bitter. Not bad - I think if this was fresh it would be better
This is the blood orange IPA. But who's counting ? White head on a orange body. Juicy as hell. Really good. Orange and so fruity
Hoppy and juicy. Really good. Grapefruit and tangy. Orange cloudy And white head. Draft at Moerlein in cincy
Black pour in the back of Jason's car in cincy. In a plastic cup. Tan head. Boozy. Cocoa and whiskey. Coffe. Good stuff
beer_name: MadTree Bourbon Barrel Aged Axis Mundi

review_blob: Had as part of a flight at their brewery in cincy. Bright orange. Tangy and fruit. Bitter and dry. Not bad
Golden pour from draft at via vite. White foamy head. Creamy for sure. Mild beer, smooth and poundable. Good for the style.
Bright orange pour from draft at via vite in cincy. White head. Really hoppy and bitter. Tons of citrus tropical fruit. Good. But very bitter finish
Black pour from draft at via vite in cincy. Malty and cocoa toasty taste. Smooth and creamy. Good beet
Orange pour with white head. Sour. Apricot and peaches. Pretty good. Had this in cincy
beer_name: Uinta Crooked Line Birthday Suit: 22nd Anniversary

review_blob: Tropical and fruity aroma. Draft at righteous in cincy. Orange with white head. Bubblegum and some mint flavor. Pretty tasty
beer_name: Stone 20th Anniversary Encore Series: 08.08.08 Vertical Epic Ale

review_blob: Black pour from draft at Righteous brothers in Cincinnati. Off white head. Graham cracker, cocoa, chalky, thick mouthfeel a little bourbon. Not bad but a mouthful to deal with for low abv
Pale orange pour from a can at OMalleys in the Alley in Cincinnati. Tons of white head. Juicy and fruity goodness. Citrus and peach with a smooth finish. Delicious.
I think it might be a little old. Tastes off and the reviews are good. A little carmel kick on a tropical dank fruit IPA. 16o can at OMalleys in the Alley in cincy
Pale orange pour from a can at OMalleys in the Alley in Cincinnati. Lemon and tropical aroma. Hoppy and dry. Bitter. Citrus. Not bad.
Orange pour from 22oz bottle at home. White head. Fruit and smoke aroma. Taste is just straight up funky. Smoke, fishy, some citrus and pine - but something kind of grosses me out about this
Black pour from 22oz bottle at home. Off white sticky/foamy head. Cocoa, chalky and malty aroma. Taste is chocolate, malts, cream, and maybe a hint of coffee. Really smooth and tasty.
beer_name: Marz Show Me What You Got

review_blob: Orange pour from 16oz bottle at home. White head. Peach and tropical aroma. Not as sour as I expected. Nice floral, hoppy, and slightly bitter farmhouse ale flavor. Smooth - delicious. One of the better Almanac Ive had.

Bright orange pour from bottle from home. Yeast and sour fruit smell. Thin white head. Nice sour and hoppy balance. More bland than Im used to in a Almanac sour, but still tasty anyway. Dry and also refreshing.
Reminds me of Hopslam sort of. Monster IIPA. Darker orange pour from draft at Sheffields. Aroma is peach and boozey. Grapefruit, tropical, hoppy and he'll and bitter. Delicious though
Draft at sheffields. Pretty bitter beer. Orange with fluffy white head. Nice pepper and grapefruit taste. No sign of "Belgium" or "white" in this for me - which I like.
Cloudy bright orange pour from bottle at home. Thin white head. Yeast and peach sour aroma. Taste is tart, tangy, acidic and peach. Pretty good brew

Solid for very low ABV, a lot of flavor considering that, not the weird session IPA aftertaste others have. Light, lemon, orange peel and fruit taste. Orange and a little cloudy pour from 22oz bottle at home. Well done.
Golden pour from 22oz bottle at home. White head. Citrus and orange aroma. Taste is juicy, fruity, refreshing - tropical and grapefruit. Yummy
Had to pour it out. It was a sad soul. Smells like cough syrup. Tastes like a skunked beer. Maybe held it too long. Yuck.
Smells like a chocolate brownie. Black with a ton of foamy tan head. 22oz bottle at home. Super cocoa and milky. Rich and coffee. Delicious
Clear orange pour from 22oz bottle at home. White foamy head. Honey, malty and sweet flavor. Very bitter finish. Hoppy. Good but not their better work.
Orange peel aroma. Tropical too. 22oz pour at home. Orange with foamy white head. Mango, pineapple and maybe some peach. Super fruity and good.
Bright orange and cloudy pour from 22oz bottle at home, tons of white foamy head. Apricot and super fruity aroma. Bubblegum, pine, dry, tropical fruits, and mild bitter finish. Delicious beer.
Brown bright pour from draft at Dryhop. White sticky and foamy head. Carmel, toffee, vanilla, and sweet. Very tasty and unique.
Juicy and delicious. Orange pour at Dryhop. Tons of sticky white head. Tangerine and grapefruit flavors. Mild hops. Love this little pal
Black thick oily pour from draft at Dryhop. Tan head. Coffee bean aroma. Coffee heavy and rich flavor. Chocolate and a little creamy. Good stuff. A nice Sunday morning beer!
beer_name: Hop Butcher The Worlds Colombian Coffee Exposition

review_blob: Black as night pour from draft at Northdown Taproom. Brown sticky head. Monster beer. Cocoa and milk aroma. Chocolate and powdered sugar flavor. Coffee notes and nuts. Superb
Super dark pour from 12oz bottle at green lady. He said its "one of a kind". Happy with his recommendation. Cherry and black berry aroma. Tart and sour. Mild tea and dunkle taste. Very good
Fantastic. Draft pour at Green Lady. White foamy head. Citrus aroma. A tropical fruit and citrus heaven bomb. Juicy and a vanilla kick. So good. My wheelhouse IPA
Black pour from draft at the Green Lady. Tan foamy head. Aroma of coffee and whiskey. Taste is sweet, vanilla, cocoa and boozy. Really good
Orange pour from draft at Bitter Pops. White foamy head. Lemon, zesty and a little bitter for a saison. Orange peel and carbonation mouthfeel. Decent
Draft at Bitter Pops. Orange with white tiny head. Hoped for better. Not a fan of this style but a huge fan of this Brewer. Has a Carmel twinge in a blonde lager flavor. Meh
Fruity for sure. Draft pour at Bitter Pops. Orange and foggy. Sour with a black berry kick. Pretty good

Bright orange pour from 16oz can at home (thx Chad!). Fluffy white head. Delicious looking glass of beer. Aroma is lemon, wheat, grass. Taste is unique but good. Vanilla, straw, hoppy and pretty bitter finish.
Black pour from 22oz bottle at home. Spicy and cocoa coffee flavor. Sweet and syrupy. Pretty good. A one glasser
Super fruity. Dry and wine tasting. Apple and tart. Carbonation. Not a fan of this
Coffee and Milky flavor. Poured from 12oz bottle at home. Creamy Oats and earthy. I like this pal
beer_name: Odd Side Ales Fight Milk Stout

review_blob: A dry tart wine taste with cherry flavor. 22oz bottle poured at home. Sweet and super flavorful. Very good.
Amazing fucking beer. Creamy coconut vanilla aroma. Sweet. Black pour from 22oz bottle at home. Cherry, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and cocoa. Nibs. Coconut dominates. So good. Top 10
